About
Miracle Garden is one of a kind in the region and in the world for such a unique display and extravagant outdoor recreational destination. Miracle Garden in its first phase is providing state-of-the-art services and facilities including open parking, VIP parking, sitting areas, prayer room, toilet blocks, ablution facility, security room, first aid room, carts for handicapped visitors, retails and commercial kiosk and all other related services available to facilitate visitors.
Duration: 2-3 hours

    A Garden Like No Other
    This was quite the place and aptly named. We have visited many gardens around the world. This one was very different than most. Massive amounts of flowers decorate large-scale displays. In typical Dubai fashion, they even do their flowers up on a grand scale! The location had huge flower arches, a castle, a Smurf village, an Emirates plane, etc. It just went on and on. Pretty incredible to see. The grounds were very clean and they offered food stands around the perimeter and shaded areas with tables to sit down and eat. It was over the top but you get used to that in Dubai. We found it quite interesting and enjoyable. Good for a nice walk with interesting visuals. Just be prepared for the incredible number of people having to take picture after picture of themselves in front of everything.

    Beautiful
    Dubai don't do things by halves, this is an absolutely phenomenal experience. Lots to see and opportunity to capture pictures. We didn't do a tour, we just grabbed cab that dropped us off at the front and the driver advised that there is a butterfly garden nearby. Similarly, when leaving there are plenty of cabs outside that are ready to pick you up. Inside there are a lot of shaded areas so you don't need to worry about it being too hot to enjoy and it is definitely a comfortable experience. Also there are plentiful areas for refreshments too. There is a small area that the local market traders try to get you to visit their shops but they are respectful when you say "no thank you" so it isn't too overwhelming and actually feels pleasant.

Myo M
Coquitlam, Canada27,109 contributions
A garden "of enchantment" :)
Jan 2024 • Solo
Without any exaggeration was a "time of enchantment" (maybe more accurately a time of "being mesmerized") at this garden with just a "vast magnitude" of colorful flowers including these vertically-displayed "hearts-with-flowers" all over the garden grounds (with actually a pathway lined with those hearts "to walk through" just shortly after entering the Garden). And, apart from the multitude of flowers are also a number of "beautiful & interesting" non-flower displays which yes although not flowers themselves are nicely decorated with leaves & flowers (large-sized sculptures of animals & "dancing maidens", a sizeable "floral clock", a tunnel-like way with "colorful umbrellas" above, and yes my favorite display I would say which is an "Emirates airplane" and which was actually likely in the past used for air transport in the country). And also, "nicely significant" I would say are the "quaint structures" in the Garden some of which resembling castles with towers & such (including one which is not so much of a structure but one with a stairway to an upper area for a pretty nice "all-around view" of the garden grounds below), and yes actually the best "in my opinion" among all those structures (of charm & quaint) is not a single structure but a collection of "colorful dwellings" called the Smurfs Village (with also a number of like life-sized figures of smurfs outside those lovely structures).

And also for a little extra cost was a worthwhile photo-op with a "small falcon" on my way out of the Garden which I arrived at by taking the bus No. 105 (just about a 15-minute ride) from the bus stop right outside the Mall of the Emirates (after first arriving there by a metro ride from the Sobha Realty metro station near the JBR Beach area where I stayed).
Written November 13, 2024

The Garden Feels Fresh - Bandya Mama
Nov 2024 • Business
Dubai Miracle Garden is truly a breathtaking experience! From the moment you step in, you’re greeted by an explosion of color and creativity. The sheer variety of flowers and intricate arrangements make it a wonderland for nature and art lovers alike. Each section is meticulously designed, with themes that range from fairytale castles to larger-than-life flower sculptures. The heart-shaped arches, towering floral displays, and vibrant pathways create a dreamy atmosphere that’s both relaxing and inspiring.
